headline: Canadian markets more impacted by tariffs than election, says Capital Economics
summary: Investing.com -- A recent report by Capital Economics has stated that tariffs are more impactful for Canadian markets than the upcoming election. The report suggests that the outlook for Canadian financial markets relies heavily on how monetary policy responds to the fallout of US tariffs, rather than potential shifts in Canadian fiscal policy.
